I"ä,<p>Update: Reftoken started trading on <a href="https://www.okex.com/spot/trade/index.do#symbol=ref_btc">OKEx</a> January 17th 2018.
<strong>__</strong><strong>__</strong><strong>__</strong>___</p>

<p>The pre-sale started on October the 2nd and the only ‚Äòrave‚Äô was a <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:6321006569584680961">short LinkedIn post stating 20% of the target of RefToken‚Äôs pre-sale hit in ~24 hours</a>. It is easy to imagine the internal conflict an average retail crypto investor must be going through though: <strong>,,B-but they did more than a colorful splash page! And they are not basement hipsters - these are actual business people, man?! Are you quite sure it is an ICO?‚Äù</strong></p>

<h4 id="what-it-is">What it is:</h4>

<p>It is called RefToken and it‚Äôs a system built on top of Ethereum blockchain.</p>

<p>The <a href="https://reftoken.io">RefToken website</a> doesn‚Äôt brand the type of affiliate business at all but you‚Äôll know where you stand the moment you look at the team behind the token.</p>

<h4 id="the-people-behind-reftoken">The people behind RefToken:</h4>

<p><strong>The team:</strong></p>

<p>CEO: Jan Sammut - <a href="https://angel.co/jan-sammut">angel.co</a>, <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jansammut/">linkedin</a>
His words: technical marketer with 10+ years experience in Real Money Gambling.</p>

<p>DEV: <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/alexanderanter/">Alexander Anter, web developer</a> and <a href="https://twitter.com/alexanderanter?lang=en">poker player</a></p>

<p>ENGINEERING: <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/lastperson/">Oleksii Matiiasevych, formerly from Tether.io</a></p>

